cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.DS

The paper discusses the lack of transparency and interpretability in deep neural network models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which focuses on the development and analysis of machine learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for disclosing a small set of training data, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of deep learning models in computer vision tasks is also mentioned, which could place the paper in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the method proposed involves constructing a boundary tree, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
